At least 102 civilians, including seven children, have been killed in the past five days, according to the UN, but the numbers could be much higher, said UN High Commissioner for Human Rights Michelle Bachelet.  "Most of the people were killed by wide-area weapons, including airstrikes and heavy artillery and multiple rocket launchers," Bachelet said, speaking before the UN Human Rights Council.  Ukrainian Ambassador to Geneva Yevgenia Filipenko says more than 350 people, including 16 children, have been killed in the five days since the invasion began, according to Ukrainian authorities.  It is currently not possible to independently confirm the exact number of victims, as is usually the case during major military conflicts.
